  "prompt": "What are some free alternatives to Aha.io?",
  "response": "There are several free or open-source alternatives to Aha.io that can help with product management, roadmapping, and project planning. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **Trello**: A flexible kanban-style project management tool that allows teams to organize tasks and projects visually. It has a free tier that can be effective for small teams.\n\n2. **Asana**: While it has premium features, Asana offers a free tier that includes task management, collaboration tools, and project tracking features.\n\n3. **ClickUp**: A highly customizable project management tool that offers a free version with features like task tracking, docs, goals, and time tracking.\n\n4. **Notion**: Notion is a versatile workspace that can be used for project management, note-taking, and documentation. The free version offers many useful features suitable for small teams.\n\n5. **Productboard**: Offers a free tier that helps teams organize product ideas and prioritize features based on customer feedback.\n\n6. **Roadmap Planner**: A tool specifically designed for creating roadmaps, with a free version that allows for basic roadmap creation.\n\n7. **Trello + Roadmap**: Use Trello combined with a roadmap-focused tool (like Roadmap Planner) to create a free product management and roadmapping solution.\n\n8. **GitHub Projects**: If your team uses GitHub for version control, GitHub Projects provides basic project management features integrated with your codebase.\n\n9. **Jira (Free Tier)**: Jira offers a free tier for small teams, which can be used for tracking issues, agile project management, and roadmap creation.\n\n10. **OpenProject**: An open-source project management tool that provides features for project planning, timelines, and task tracking.\n\n11. **Wrike**: Provides a free version for small teams with basic task and project management features.\n\nThese alternatives vary in their specific features and capabilities, so it's a good idea to explore a few to see which best meets your team's specific needs.",
